WHILE ATTEMPTING A TOUCH AND GO LDG DURING A STUDENT SOLO CROSS 
COUNTRY FLIGHT, DIRECTIONAL CONTROL WAS LOST DURING THE TAKEOFF PHASE ON 
THE SNOW PACKED RUNWAY. THE STUDENT PILOT SAID HE HAD NEVER LANDED 
AND TAKEN OFF UNDER THOSE RUNWAY CONDITIONS. THE AIRCRAFT SWERVED TO THE 
LEFT, COLLIDED WITH A SNOW BANK AND FLIPPED INVERTED, SUBSTANTIALLY 
DAMAGING THE AIRCRAFT. 
